executive officer  hov nd qtr k there’s a reason ara hovnanian dumped  shares of hov stock on april th  – insider stock selling ahead of an earnings disaster hovnanian greeted the stock market this morning with a big earnings miss  it’s stock plunged as much as  i may have been a bit early in forecasting my demise of the housing market but i know i’m right  hov is the th largest homebuilder in the country  it sells homes in  states including the largest housing markets for new homes like california texas and florida   hov primarily sells into the firsttime and moveup buyer market  in other words it’s q results are a good barometer of the market for new home sales in general although it’s revenues were higher thanks to the bubble in new home prices hov’s gross margins plunged  basis points from  last year in q to  in its latest quarter this is due to the expense associated with started but unsold homes a feature that is endemic to every homebuilder i research  it’s total unit home deliveries dropped  vs the q  it’s cost of sales also includes over  million inventory and land option writeoffs vs k in q  while not large relative to its total cost of sales inventory and land writeoffs are going to become a recurring feature with every homebuilder going forward despite a decline in home deliveries hov ballooned its inventory by  million in the last six months  billion in oct  vs  billion at the end of the most recent quarter inventories at all of the homebuilders have swelled up to record levels – even highher than at the peak of the big housing bubble this is despite the fact that unit sales volume is roughly  of peak unit sales volume an even more shocking fact is that the amount of debt per housing unit sold at every homebuilder is several times higher than it was at the peak of the housing bubble for instance at  billion hov’s debt load has increased  million in the last six months on a trailing  month basis hov has delivered  homes this translates into  of debt per home unit delivered i have always predicted that hov would be the first homebuilder to hit the wall  this is why i have not published a research report on the company it’s stock has been below  since late  it’s not worth shorting however i have published indepth research reports on the two stocks that i think are most likely to follow hov into the bankruptcy abyss  both of these companies have operating and financial profiles which are quite similar to that of hov  both of these stocks plunged and then rebounded about six months ago  i believe that we will see them plunge and stay down at some point in the next  months  the problem is you have to positioned ahead of the plunge or you will miss it you can access the report for either company here   i will have more on this later but now the legacy home equity loans left over from the big housing bubble are going to start torpedoing the financial system no one has thought about these roadside financial exploding devices but starting in mid and ballooning up quickly from there home equity loans sitting dormant other than a small monthly interest payment have been and will be converting to fixedrate amortizing nd mortgages the monthly payment on these will double or triple for most homeowners with helocs resetting the amount sitting on bank balance sheets is over a half trillion dollars for its quarter ended march  the delinquency rate on its heloc balances jumped  just when mom and pop home flippers were thinking that the water was nice and warm they are going to get ripped apart by a new wave of distressed home sellers and foreclosure auctions for the record i search for home listings on just one zip code in central denver i am now getting at least one “new price” email per day including three yesterday and one today already the next leg down in the housing market is starting… share thistweet related  thoughts on “hovnanian ushers in the next housing market collapse” this is merely my own observation so take it as tha